00:00:11.454 --> 00:00:19.422 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.422 --> 00:00:21.414 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:21.414 --> 00:00:24.420 align:middle line:90%


00:00:24.420 --> 00:00:28.530 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA GARR: Whenever you find
yourself encountering division,

00:00:28.530 --> 00:00:31.500 align:middle line:10%
whenever you observe yourself
feeling isolated or needing

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:37.080 align:middle line:10%
to withdraw from the people
or the situations around you,

00:00:37.080 --> 00:00:39.570 align:middle line:10%
Native American
author Anita Sanchez

00:00:39.570 --> 00:00:44.470 align:middle line:10%
invites you to remember,
there is another way to live.

00:00:44.470 --> 00:00:45.430 align:middle line:90%
Hi, I'm Lisa Garr.

00:00:45.430 --> 00:00:49.450 align:middle line:84%
And joining me is Anita Sanchez
to share her four sacred gifts.

00:00:49.450 --> 00:00:52.180 align:middle line:10%
They guide us to live
as one human race,

00:00:52.180 --> 00:00:55.150 align:middle line:10%
as our ancestors and our
elders have taught us to live.

00:00:55.150 --> 00:00:56.110 align:middle line:90%
Hello.

00:00:56.110 --> 00:00:57.460 align:middle line:90%
>>ANITA SANCHEZ: Hello, Lisa.

00:00:57.460 --> 00:00:58.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You're amazing.

00:00:58.480 --> 00:01:05.140 align:middle line:84%
You have this 40-year history
of organizational development

00:01:05.140 --> 00:01:07.060 align:middle line:90%
in the corporate world.

00:01:07.060 --> 00:01:10.150 align:middle line:84%
And yet, you have this
great deep history

00:01:10.150 --> 00:01:11.950 align:middle line:90%
in the Native American arts.

00:01:11.950 --> 00:01:14.500 align:middle line:84%
Tell me a little bit
about your corporate life.

00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:17.024 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes-- well, I
knew from a little girl

00:01:17.024 --> 00:01:18.940 align:middle line:84%
that I was going to grow
up and connect people

00:01:18.940 --> 00:01:19.740 align:middle line:90%
all over the world.

00:01:19.740 --> 00:01:21.260 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know it was corporate.

00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.250 align:middle line:10%
I'm the first one in my family
to be involved in corporations.

00:01:24.250 --> 00:01:27.320 align:middle line:10%
And so-- yes, for 42 years--

00:01:27.320 --> 00:01:29.810 align:middle line:10%
I just celebrated-- I've
had my own business.

00:01:29.810 --> 00:01:30.610 align:middle line:90%
And I go in.

00:01:30.610 --> 00:01:34.540 align:middle line:84%
And I consult from the
C-suite to newbies coming in.

00:01:34.540 --> 00:01:38.590 align:middle line:84%
And it's basically sharing about
how to work and live together--

00:01:38.590 --> 00:01:41.680 align:middle line:84%
how to really appreciate each
other's gifts-- the differences

00:01:41.680 --> 00:01:43.070 align:middle line:90%
as well as the similarities.

00:01:43.070 --> 00:01:44.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's so needed.

00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:47.590 align:middle line:84%
So were you the first in
your family to get a PhD

00:01:47.590 --> 00:01:50.757 align:middle line:84%
and to go to that level
of schooling as well?

00:01:50.757 --> 00:01:52.840 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes, I was first
in quite a few things.

00:01:52.840 --> 00:01:55.919 align:middle line:84%
So yes, definitely, I'm a first
generation to go to college

00:01:55.919 --> 00:01:58.210 align:middle line:84%
and then going on to get my
master's-- and first to get

00:01:58.210 --> 00:01:59.350 align:middle line:90%
a PhD.

00:01:59.350 --> 00:02:01.600 align:middle line:84%
And I have 120
first cousins, so--

00:02:01.600 --> 00:02:02.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my goodness.

00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:05.080 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes-- so when I go
back for reunions and that,

00:02:05.080 --> 00:02:06.420 align:middle line:90%
I'm always reminded.

00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:08.330 align:middle line:84%
And some of them, I
don't even know anymore.

00:02:08.330 --> 00:02:09.850 align:middle line:90%
They're the kids' kids.

00:02:09.850 --> 00:02:12.310 align:middle line:10%
And they're like,
you let me know

00:02:12.310 --> 00:02:13.870 align:middle line:10%
that I could go and do this.

00:02:13.870 --> 00:02:15.040 align:middle line:10%
You were the one.

00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:17.090 align:middle line:10%
So it's amazing responsibility.

00:02:17.090 --> 00:02:19.020 align:middle line:10%
But I'll tell you,
it's a much bigger joy.

00:02:19.020 --> 00:02:19.885 align:middle line:90%
It's so wonderful.

00:02:19.885 --> 00:02:22.773 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It must be, to
inspire generations.

00:02:22.773 --> 00:02:23.890 align:middle line:90%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes-- yes.

00:02:23.890 --> 00:02:24.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's incredible--

00:02:24.540 --> 00:02:25.340 align:middle line:90%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes.

00:02:25.340 --> 00:02:27.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --Dr. Anita.

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:28.780 align:middle line:84%
So tell me a little
bit about that.

00:02:28.780 --> 00:02:32.770 align:middle line:84%
42 years ago, you
started your own business

00:02:32.770 --> 00:02:36.490 align:middle line:84%
as a Native American
Mexican-American woman.

00:02:36.490 --> 00:02:37.870 align:middle line:90%
How was that?

00:02:37.870 --> 00:02:41.166 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: Well, I had
a lot of disbelievers.

00:02:41.166 --> 00:02:43.540 align:middle line:84%
Some of the faculty, when I
said what I was going to do--

00:02:43.540 --> 00:02:46.550 align:middle line:84%
not all of them, but
some of them were like--

00:02:46.550 --> 00:02:49.480 align:middle line:84%
and I know they were coming
out of their own story,

00:02:49.480 --> 00:02:50.280 align:middle line:90%
as we all do.

00:02:50.280 --> 00:02:51.779 align:middle line:84%
And that's why it's
really important

00:02:51.779 --> 00:02:54.470 align:middle line:84%
to listen to each other, to
expand our stories and find out

00:02:54.470 --> 00:02:55.636 align:middle line:90%
there's another possibility.

00:02:55.636 --> 00:02:57.530 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, they said,
you can't do that.

00:02:57.530 --> 00:02:59.670 align:middle line:84%
What do you mean, you're going
to go and work internationally?

00:02:59.670 --> 00:03:01.380 align:middle line:84%
I said, no, that's
what I'm going to do.

00:03:01.380 --> 00:03:02.830 align:middle line:90%
And they're like, no, no, no.

00:03:02.830 --> 00:03:06.110 align:middle line:84%
You go to other colleges, other
universities than Colorado,

00:03:06.110 --> 00:03:08.039 align:middle line:84%
so that you can get
a faculty position.

00:03:08.039 --> 00:03:09.830 align:middle line:84%
Because a Mexican and
Native American woman

00:03:09.830 --> 00:03:11.329 align:middle line:84%
is not going to own
her own business

00:03:11.329 --> 00:03:13.070 align:middle line:90%
and travel all over the world.

00:03:13.070 --> 00:03:14.390 align:middle line:90%
Well, I'm 23.

00:03:14.390 --> 00:03:15.190 align:middle line:90%
And I'm traveling.

00:03:15.190 --> 00:03:17.090 align:middle line:84%
I find myself in
Singapore, working

00:03:17.090 --> 00:03:19.760 align:middle line:84%
with women whose countries
are at war with each other,

00:03:19.760 --> 00:03:23.970 align:middle line:84%
doing visionaring work
and peace and development.

00:03:23.970 --> 00:03:27.380 align:middle line:84%
I'm in corporations-- Hewlett
Packard, Dupont, AT&T.

00:03:27.380 --> 00:03:28.790 align:middle line:90%
The list goes on.

00:03:28.790 --> 00:03:29.690 align:middle line:90%
And-- yeah.

00:03:29.690 --> 00:03:30.773 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What would you do?

00:03:30.773 --> 00:03:32.490 align:middle line:84%
What would you do
when you get there?

00:03:32.490 --> 00:03:35.240 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: Well, you always
contract with the executives.

00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:38.880 align:middle line:84%
And I remember, one of my
first ones, sitting there.

00:03:38.880 --> 00:03:41.660 align:middle line:84%
At that point, I think it was
26 in this particular client I'm

00:03:41.660 --> 00:03:42.470 align:middle line:90%
thinking of.

00:03:42.470 --> 00:03:43.130 align:middle line:90%
And I'm sitting there.

00:03:43.130 --> 00:03:44.088 align:middle line:90%
And he's looking at me.

00:03:44.088 --> 00:03:45.912 align:middle line:84%
He goes, I knew
you were a woman.

00:03:45.912 --> 00:03:47.870 align:middle line:84%
I knew from your name,
you're probably Mexican.

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:50.090 align:middle line:90%
You look Native American.

00:03:50.090 --> 00:03:52.070 align:middle line:90%
But you're so young.

00:03:52.070 --> 00:03:53.600 align:middle line:90%
What are you going to teach me?

00:03:53.600 --> 00:03:58.130 align:middle line:84%
And I remember looking at
him and saying, I don't know.

00:03:58.130 --> 00:03:59.900 align:middle line:90%
Do you want to find out?

00:03:59.900 --> 00:04:02.300 align:middle line:90%
And he just was like, yes--

00:04:02.300 --> 00:04:04.100 align:middle line:90%
yes, let's stay.

00:04:04.100 --> 00:04:04.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: My goodness.

00:04:04.980 --> 00:04:07.230 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes, but I teach
them all sorts of things--

00:04:07.230 --> 00:04:13.520 align:middle line:84%
of how to build effective teams,
how to go inside and find out

00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:15.390 align:middle line:90%
what really is your purpose--

00:04:15.390 --> 00:04:18.410 align:middle line:84%
what it is that
really is calling you.

00:04:18.410 --> 00:04:20.870 align:middle line:84%
Because there's
all sorts of crises

00:04:20.870 --> 00:04:23.690 align:middle line:84%
in corporations-- in any
business, whatever size it is.

00:04:23.690 --> 00:04:27.742 align:middle line:84%
But when you're clear about
your vision and your purpose,

00:04:27.742 --> 00:04:29.200 align:middle line:84%
when you know what's
being called--

00:04:29.200 --> 00:04:30.870 align:middle line:90%
and that can shift over time--

00:04:30.870 --> 00:04:32.762 align:middle line:84%
you're able to
move through those.

00:04:32.762 --> 00:04:34.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you go
into environments

00:04:34.220 --> 00:04:37.140 align:middle line:84%
where there is a need for
organizational development

00:04:37.140 --> 00:04:37.940 align:middle line:90%
and consulting.

00:04:37.940 --> 00:04:38.210 align:middle line:90%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes.

00:04:38.210 --> 00:04:39.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So there's usually
something that's broken.

00:04:39.930 --> 00:04:41.450 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes,
there usually is.

00:04:41.450 --> 00:04:44.150 align:middle line:84%
Usually-- because
one of my big loves

00:04:44.150 --> 00:04:45.710 align:middle line:90%
is diversity and inclusion.

00:04:45.710 --> 00:04:48.140 align:middle line:84%
So it's generally, oh,
we're losing the women.

00:04:48.140 --> 00:04:49.850 align:middle line:90%
We're losing the Black folks.

00:04:49.850 --> 00:04:51.740 align:middle line:90%
We can't attract the Latinos.

00:04:51.740 --> 00:04:54.335 align:middle line:84%
Oh my-- and they're
expanding all over the world.

00:04:54.335 --> 00:04:56.210 align:middle line:84%
So how do we get them
to work with each other

00:04:56.210 --> 00:04:58.610 align:middle line:90%
across the differences.

00:04:58.610 --> 00:05:02.420 align:middle line:84%
And mostly, they're racial,
gender, sexual orientation--

00:05:02.420 --> 00:05:06.710 align:middle line:84%
but they move beyond that
too into what I would call--

00:05:06.710 --> 00:05:09.500 align:middle line:84%
it's more subtle, but
ever so presence--

00:05:09.500 --> 00:05:13.700 align:middle line:84%
which is the differences
in world views, which

00:05:13.700 --> 00:05:15.680 align:middle line:84%
makes it or breaks
it of whether it's

00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:17.750 align:middle line:84%
going to be easy
to dance together,

00:05:17.750 --> 00:05:22.670 align:middle line:84%
to make those profits, to
obtain and exceed those goals.

00:05:22.670 --> 00:05:25.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And often, there
is history attached to it--

00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:27.980 align:middle line:84%
decades, generational
history that's

00:05:27.980 --> 00:05:30.260 align:middle line:84%
attached to these
different perspectives.

00:05:30.260 --> 00:05:33.200 align:middle line:84%
How do you address that
to bring everyone together

00:05:33.200 --> 00:05:34.430 align:middle line:90%
for a greater whole?

00:05:34.430 --> 00:05:36.860 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes-- well,
first, you listen.

00:05:36.860 --> 00:05:38.910 align:middle line:90%
You allow-- you welcome it.

00:05:38.910 --> 00:05:40.370 align:middle line:84%
So I remember, in
the early days--

00:05:40.370 --> 00:05:41.990 align:middle line:84%
it's going to date
me a little bit--

00:05:41.990 --> 00:05:44.201 align:middle line:84%
but when I would go
into corporations

00:05:44.201 --> 00:05:46.700 align:middle line:84%
and I would get the contract,
they'd go, before we sign now,

00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:48.770 align:middle line:84%
there's two things
you can never do here.

00:05:48.770 --> 00:05:49.820 align:middle line:90%
You have to agree.

00:05:49.820 --> 00:05:51.250 align:middle line:90%
I'd go, well, what are those?

00:05:51.250 --> 00:05:53.460 align:middle line:84%
And they'd repeat
those for decades.

00:05:53.460 --> 00:05:54.920 align:middle line:90%
You can't talk about politics.

00:05:54.920 --> 00:05:56.960 align:middle line:84%
These are US international
corporations.

00:05:56.960 --> 00:05:59.180 align:middle line:90%
You can't talk about politics.

00:05:59.180 --> 00:06:00.680 align:middle line:84%
And you can't talk
about religion.

00:06:00.680 --> 00:06:02.550 align:middle line:90%
And I would say, fine.

00:06:02.550 --> 00:06:05.360 align:middle line:84%
I don't need to talk about
politics, although we can

00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:07.760 align:middle line:90%
have those side conversations.

00:06:07.760 --> 00:06:11.870 align:middle line:84%
But when you say religion, I
think people confuse things.

00:06:11.870 --> 00:06:15.530 align:middle line:84%
I will always deal
with spirituality.

00:06:15.530 --> 00:06:18.380 align:middle line:90%
We all come in with spirit.

00:06:18.380 --> 00:06:20.930 align:middle line:90%
We choose religions.

00:06:20.930 --> 00:06:23.876 align:middle line:84%
I can not talk about
religion, but I can't not

00:06:23.876 --> 00:06:24.875 align:middle line:90%
talk about spirituality.

00:06:24.875 --> 00:06:25.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:06:25.160 --> 00:06:26.600 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: And I'd
lose some contracts.

00:06:26.600 --> 00:06:28.450 align:middle line:84%
So some of my colleagues
go, why did you do that?

00:06:28.450 --> 00:06:29.250 align:middle line:90%
Those were big!

00:06:29.250 --> 00:06:32.690 align:middle line:84%
And I'd be like,
because if I'm there

00:06:32.690 --> 00:06:36.560 align:middle line:84%
to help them become
whole, effective, then

00:06:36.560 --> 00:06:38.360 align:middle line:84%
I can't cut out a
whole piece of--

00:06:38.360 --> 00:06:38.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You-- who you are.

00:06:38.700 --> 00:06:40.180 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: --this
other being, right?

00:06:40.180 --> 00:06:40.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:06:40.460 --> 00:06:42.390 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: And who I
am-- so it wouldn't work.

00:06:42.390 --> 00:06:43.730 align:middle line:90%
But it changed.

00:06:43.730 --> 00:06:47.660 align:middle line:84%
By 2002, I never
heard that again.

00:06:47.660 --> 00:06:49.417 align:middle line:84%
And in those who
did bring it up,

00:06:49.417 --> 00:06:50.750 align:middle line:90%
I'd say what I just said to you.

00:06:50.750 --> 00:06:53.390 align:middle line:90%
And they'd go, OK.

00:06:53.390 --> 00:06:54.612 align:middle line:90%
So things are changing--

00:06:54.612 --> 00:06:55.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's great to know.

00:06:55.820 --> 00:06:58.069 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: --to understand
we're spiritual beings too.

00:06:58.069 --> 00:06:59.900 align:middle line:84%
Yes, we're physical,
mental, emotional.

00:06:59.900 --> 00:07:02.690 align:middle line:84%
But this spirit is
really critical.

00:07:02.690 --> 00:07:06.045 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, you didn't just
learn this from going to school

00:07:06.045 --> 00:07:06.920 align:middle line:90%
and getting your PhD.

00:07:06.920 --> 00:07:07.220 align:middle line:90%
>>SANCHEZ: No.

00:07:07.220 --> 00:07:08.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Tell me a little
bit about your family,

00:07:08.750 --> 00:07:09.620 align:middle line:90%
your background.

00:07:09.620 --> 00:07:12.592 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: Yes, well,
I was really fortunate.

00:07:12.592 --> 00:07:15.030 align:middle line:84%
In growing up, being
part indigenous--

00:07:15.030 --> 00:07:17.810 align:middle line:84%
Aztecan-- maternal
grandmother is Aztecan.

00:07:17.810 --> 00:07:19.180 align:middle line:90%
And so she would always--

00:07:19.180 --> 00:07:22.700 align:middle line:84%
from a little girl, I remember
doing ceremony and just

00:07:22.700 --> 00:07:25.220 align:middle line:84%
wonderful things
about understanding

00:07:25.220 --> 00:07:26.180 align:middle line:90%
that we're spirit.

00:07:26.180 --> 00:07:27.950 align:middle line:84%
But we're spirit--
we're reinforced

00:07:27.950 --> 00:07:29.330 align:middle line:90%
by connection to everything.

00:07:29.330 --> 00:07:30.130 align:middle line:90%
I have to tell you.

00:07:30.130 --> 00:07:31.340 align:middle line:90%
It just popped up for me.

00:07:31.340 --> 00:07:33.624 align:middle line:84%
One of the things
that I loved so much

00:07:33.624 --> 00:07:35.540 align:middle line:84%
was, when we were all
little-- a bunch of us--

00:07:35.540 --> 00:07:36.998 align:middle line:84%
and we were playing
outside all day

00:07:36.998 --> 00:07:38.810 align:middle line:84%
long-- she got us
up really early.

00:07:38.810 --> 00:07:41.127 align:middle line:84%
And as soon as the sun
hit those sunflowers,

00:07:41.127 --> 00:07:41.960 align:middle line:90%
we stood over there.

00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:44.490 align:middle line:84%
And she had to stand there for
a while-- like, five minutes.

00:07:44.490 --> 00:07:46.460 align:middle line:84%
We were little, so we
couldn't stand too long.

00:07:46.460 --> 00:07:47.260 align:middle line:90%
And then we'd play.

00:07:47.260 --> 00:07:49.680 align:middle line:84%
And then, I think, it must
have been every hour or so.

00:07:49.680 --> 00:07:50.480 align:middle line:90%
She would come out.

00:07:50.480 --> 00:07:51.410 align:middle line:90%
And we'd turn.

00:07:51.410 --> 00:07:54.170 align:middle line:84%
And that day, I
experienced what it

00:07:54.170 --> 00:07:56.550 align:middle line:84%
was to be connected
to a sunflower--

00:07:56.550 --> 00:07:57.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:07:57.350 --> 00:07:59.180 align:middle line:84%
>>SANCHEZ: --to understand,
no matter what was happening

00:07:59.180 --> 00:07:59.980 align:middle line:90%
in the day--

00:07:59.980 --> 00:08:03.050 align:middle line:84%
whether I fell down or
somebody was fussy or everybody

00:08:03.050 --> 00:08:06.390 align:middle line:84%
was having fun-- that you
can always look to the sun.

00:08:06.390 --> 00:08:09.710 align:middle line:84%
And so that kind of
understanding or listening

00:08:09.710 --> 00:08:11.780 align:middle line:84%
to yourself but
also understanding

